The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Bata net profit jumps to Rs 4.4 cr

 OUR BUREAU

 April 26: Bata Indias net profit has jumped to Rs 4.41 crore in the first quarter ended March 31 from Rs 50 lakh in the same period last year.

 The sharp rise in profit came despite a marginal loss in sales during the period.

 Net sales stood at Rs 165.13 crore compared with Rs 167.49 crore in the same period last year.

 The companys bottomline has improved because of cost efficiency and better financial management.

 Total expenditure was down to Rs 155.65 crore from Rs 160.97 crore in the year-ago period.

 The company reduced its staff strength last year by offering VRS to around 1,000 employees at a cost of Rs 5 crore.

 Interest cost also went down to Rs 1.78 crore from Rs 2.56 crore last year. 

 Bata has posted a net profit of Rs 12.50 crore during 2005 against a loss of Rs 62.75 crore in the previous year.

 The companys total income, however, showed a marginal rise to Rs 725.39 crore from Rs 698.49 crore.

 The companys board did not recommend any dividend today.

 Godrej Consumer

 Godrej Consumer Products Ltd today reported a 4.64 per cent growth in net profit at Rs 30.16 crore for the fourth quarter ended March 31, 2006, compared with Rs 28.82 crore in the same period previous fiscal.

 Total income rose 14.46 per cent to Rs 164.78 crore against Rs 143.96 crore in the year-ago period, the company informed Bombay Stock Exchange.

 The board has declared a fourth interim dividend of 125 per cent, or Rs 5 on shares of Rs 4 each, for 2005-06. 




